{
    "id": "electronics/check-battery-voltage",
    "title": "Check a battery pack's voltage",
    "description": "Use a digital multimeter to check a 12 V LiFePO4 battery pack after disconnecting it and placing it on a dry, non-conductive surface. Wear safety goggles throughout.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/electronics_check_battery_pack_voltage.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Before measuring, isolate the LiFePO4 pack on a dry non-conductive surface, inspect for swelling/cracks, and wear safety goggles. If damage is visible, do not test—quarantine the pack.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "measure",
                    "text": "Pack looks safe to measure."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "safety-stop",
                    "text": "I found damage or heat."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "safety-stop",
            "text": "Correct call. Do not probe a damaged pack. Move it to a fire-safe container, label it for disposal, and only continue this quest with a known-safe replacement battery.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "start",
                    "text": "Replacement pack ready; restart safety check."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "measure",
            "text": "Set the multimeter to 20 V DC, confirm leads are in voltage ports, and keep fingers behind probe guards. Measure red-to-positive, black-to-negative. Record the exact value before deciding pass/fail.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "interpret",
                    "text": "Recorded 12.4 V to 13.6 V (in-range).",
                    "process": "measure-battery-voltage",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "cfe87611-623a-45b0-9243-422cd8a73a16",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "5127e156-3009-4db4-85ac-e3ea070b68f2",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "c9b51052-4594-42d7-a723-82b815ab8cc2",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "corrective",
                    "text": "Recorded outside 12.4-13.6 V.",
                    "process": "measure-battery-voltage",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "cfe87611-623a-45b0-9243-422cd8a73a16",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "5127e156-3009-4db4-85ac-e3ea070b68f2",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "c9b51052-4594-42d7-a723-82b815ab8cc2",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "corrective",
            "text": "Out-of-range response: if below 12.4 V, place the pack on a compatible charger and re-check after charge stabilization. If above 13.6 V off charger, isolate and inspect for charger faults before reuse. Always re-test before closure.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "measure",
                    "text": "Corrective action done. Re-test now."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "interpret",
            "text": "Interpretation checkpoint: your reading is inside the 12.4-13.6 V acceptance band for a resting 12 V LiFePO4 pack. Confirm terminals stayed cool and no arcing occurred.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "Reading and safety checks both passed."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "corrective",
                    "text": "I need corrective action before sign-off."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Nice work. Remove probes, power down the meter, and store the battery in a dry fire-safe location with measured voltage noted for maintenance history.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Voltage check complete."
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
